            <biogHist>
                <p>Angus MacEachen was the son of farmer Ronald and Catherine MacEachen n√©e
                    Macpherson in Torlum. In 1867 he married Marion Macpherson in Torlum. He worked
                    as a grocer, or 'merchant' as documented in the 1891 census, but is described as
                    a crofter by the time of his death. </p>
                <p>He died of pleurisy at the age of 65 and his son Ranald MacEachen witnessed the
                    certificate. </p>
                <p>He is mentioned in a story told to Alexander Carmichael by John Ewen MacRury in
                    1895, the year of MacEachen's death.</p>
